Authorities in various countries are struggling to keep pace with technological advancements like YouTube, a platform for sharing videos online.
Reporters Without Borders highlighted China as a major jailer of cyber-dissidents, sparking concerns about the global spread of its Internet censorship model.
Recent cyber attacks on domain name servers raised alarms about Internet security, with experts emphasizing the need for improved IT security measures.
The rise of botnets, malicious software that hijacks computers for criminal activities, poses a significant threat to online security.
Companies are investing heavily in infrastructure upgrades to combat escalating cyber threats and ensure a secure online environment.
